3 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Government evidence data and impact commission. (1) There is a
4 government evidence data and impact commission.
5 (2) (a) The commission consists of the following voting members:
6 (i) the presiding officer of the senate finance and claims committee or the officer's designee;
7 (ii) the presiding officer of the house appropriations committee or the officer's designee;
8 (iii) the majority presiding officer and the minority vice presiding officer of the legislative audit
9 committee or their designees;
10 (iv) a member of the modernization and risk analysis committee appointed by the presiding officer
11 of the legislative finance committee;
12 (v) a member of the legislature appointed by the governor who is from the opposite party of the
13 member from the modernization and risk analysis committee;
14 (vi) the budget director or the director’s designee;
15 (vii) the director of the department of administration or the director’s designee;
16 (viii) the director of the office of state public defender or the director’s designee;
17 (ix) two directors of a state agency appointed by the governor or their designees; and
18 (x) one member of the public appointed by the governor.
19 (b) The commission consists of the following ex officio, nonvoting members:
20 (i) the legislative fiscal analyst;
21 (ii) the legislative auditor:
22 (iii) a staff member from the legislative services division's legal services office;
23 (iv) a deputy budget director; and
24 (v) the chief data officer.
25 (3) Appointed members of the commission must be compensated and receive travel expenses as
26 provided for in 2-15-124 for each day in attendance at commission meetings or in the performance of any duty
27 or service as a commission member.
