14 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Purpose. (1) The commission is charged with developing a system of
15 evidence and impact analysis and with making recommendations for the implementation of the analysis on
16 executive and legislative decisionmaking and recommending a system for the collection and integration of
17 targeted data for use by the legislature and the executive branch in analyzing outcomes of the agency
18 programs, effective use of state resources, and efficient administration of state government.
19 (2) The system developed must allow policymakers to identify inefficient, redundant, and
20 antiquated programs in state government. A report of an evidence and impact analysis conducted using the
21 developed system may include recommendations for improvements in the analyzed programs.
22
